com.insose.gae.pager
Class GaeQuery

java.lang.Object
  com.insose.gae.pager.GaeQuery

public class GaeQuery
extends java.lang.Object

Standalone representation of a query. The query can be built using a string literal of a limited JDOQL syntax, or programatically.

Create an empty JDO query that will be configured programatically.

Parameters:
kind - The base JDO kind.
uniquePropertyName - Name of the unique property, it doesn't have to be the primary key.
paging - Whether paging should be used. The pager only accepts paging queries.

GaeQuery

public GaeQuery(java.lang.String entityKind,
                java.lang.String uniquePropertyName,
                boolean paging,
                java.lang.Class<?> parentIndexKind)
Create an empty low-level API query, to be configured programatically.

Parameters:
entityKind - The kind of the low-level Entity. Instances of this Entity must be ancestors of the JDO parentIndexKind parameter.
uniquePropertyName - Name of the unique property, it doesn't have to be the primary key.
paging - Whether paging should be used. The pager only accepts paging queries.
parentIndexKind - The JDO kind the pager will return, when executing this query.

GaeQuery

public GaeQuery(GaeQuery base)
Create a new query based on an existing one. Only base parameters are reused. The Orders and Filters must be configured from scratch.

Parameters:
base - The GaeQuery to base this new query on.

GaeQuery

public GaeQuery(java.lang.Class<?> kind,
                java.lang.String uniquePropertyName,
                PageDirection direction,
                java.lang.String queryString,
                java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> paramVals,
                java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> bookmark,
                boolean paging)
Create a new query from a limited substet of JDOQL syntax.

query:
[[WHERE filters] [PARAMETERS parameters]] [ORDER BY orders]
filters:
filter [&& filters]
filter:
properyName operator parameterName
operator:
one of: < <= == > >=
parameters:
parameter [, parameters]
parameter:
javaTypeName parameterName
orders:
order [, orders]
order:
propertyName [ASC | DESC]

Parameters:
kind - The base JDO kind.
uniquePropertyName - Name of the unique property, it doesn't have to be the primary key.
direction - The direction the pager will use.
queryString - The query string.
paramVals - Map with values for the parameters declared in the query.
bookmark - This map is managed by the pager. It must be empty at the start of the paging.
paging - Whether paging should be used. The pager only accepts paging queries.
